caption.paragraph:
FIGURE 8.

Brachypeplus binotatus

, orig. A-B: specimen from NSW (“… Lilyvale…”); 
A
: body, dorsal; 
B
: shoulder part of elytron, dorsal; C, E, G, I: specimen from NSW (“… Lansdowne S.F…”); 
C
: male anal sclerite and 
spiculum gastrale
, ventral; 
E
: tegmen, ventral; 
G
: penis trunk, dorsal; 
I
: proximal part of inner sac with armature; D, F, H, J: specimen from QLD (“… env. Ingham …”); 
D
: male anal sclerite and 
spiculum gastrale
, ventral; 
F
: tegmen, ventral; 
H
: penis trunk, dorsal; 
J
: proximal part of inner sac with armature; 
L
: ovipositor, ventral; specimen from ACT (“… Tidbinbilla Nat.Pk…”). Scale bars: 
a
= 1.0 mm to Fig. A; 
b
= 0.5 mm to Fig. B; 
с
= 0.25 mm to Figs C–L.
